## 4. SIGNAL FIRING — How Extracted Data Becomes Alpha

### Currently Wired (✅)

```
FedRSSCalendarPoller.poll_speeches()
  → DiffbotExtractor.extract_article(speech_url)
  → SentimentAnalyzer.analyze(text_chunk, speaker)
  → FedComment(sentiment=HAWKISH/DOVISH/NEUTRAL)
  → engine.py saves to DB
  → signal_generator._apply_holistic_kill_shots()
      → Compares fed_tone vs dark_pool_volume
      → divergence_score += 7 if mismatch
      → VETO or BOOST the trade signal
```

### Not Yet Wired (🔲)

```
PoliticianMonitor.poll_latest_trades()
  → ✅ Extracted via Diffbot + BS4 fallback
  → ✅ Stored in politician_trades table (MD5 dedup)
  → ✅ Queried by signal_generator → divergence_score += 2 when pol buys + DP spike

InsiderMonitor.poll_latest_trades()
  → ✅ Extracted via BS4 (tinytable class)
  → ✅ Stored in insider_trades table (MD5 dedup)
  → ✅ Queried by signal_generator → divergence_score += 3 when cluster buys + DP spike
  → ✅ divergence_score -= 2 when insider exits > buys

EconMonitor (doesn't exist yet)
  → ❌ No surprise calculation (actual vs consensus)
  → ❌ Not connected to NarrativeEngine
```

